************************
*  Conky Configuration *
************************

Conky is a system monitor, which can be manually configured

1. Create a file named .conkyrc in your home directory
2.1. Then, you need to figure out how to use its syntax
2.2. Check out config files on the Internet, or use my theme: https://github.com/damoklov/conky-minimal
3. Run conky from your terminal or application menu: 
   $ conky -d
4. Edit config file .conkyrc while conky is running on the background
5. Save document to see changes (CTRL+S)
6. Go on and experiment!
